<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-130-385 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 824 574</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computergram International  June 11 1991 n1694* Full Text COPYRIGHT Apt Data Services (UK) 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Calculus has board and software for server-based facsimilecapability. (Calculus Inc.'s Advanced EZ-FaxLAN facsimile board)(product announcement)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Calculus Inc. (Product introduction).andO;Product:   Advanced EZ-FaxLAN (Communications software) (Productintroduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionCompatible SoftwareFacsimile boards/cards.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>CALCULUS HAS BOARD AND SOFTWARE FORandM;SERVER-BASED FACSIMILE CAPABILITYandM;Sunnyvale, California-based Calculus Inc has introduced the AdvancedEZ-FaxLAN - a local area network facsimile board with facsimile server andworkstation software.andP;  The new package features Hewlett-Packard Co LaserJetcompatibility for laser-quality faxing, facsimile send and receive capabilityfrom any workstation, and optimised RAM configuration, leaving maximum memoryallocation for the network operating system and main application.andP;  AdvancedEZ-FaxLAN has been certified for Novell Inc's NetWare and Artisoft Inc'sLANtastic network operating systems, and also operates on 3Com Inc's 3andplus;,Microsoft Corp's LAN Manager, IBM Corp's PC LAN, Banyan Systems Inc's Vines,CBIS Network-OS, Ungermann-Bass Inc One, and other MS-Net based networks.andO;The card has a &quot;fax-as-you-print&quot; design philosophy, although facsimilecreation and transmission is identical to normal document creation andprinting from any MS-DOS application - for example, from WordPerfect 5.1 theuser composes a high-quality, mixed-mode text and graphics document, which is&quot;printed&quot; through WordPerfect to LPT3, which is configured as a phantomprinter port, operating as an additional network HP LaserJet.andP;  The print jobis intercepted and the fax card transmits the document as a laser-qualityfax.andP;  Soft-fonts can be downloaded to Advanced EZ-FaxLAN, and are retained aslong as the computer remains powered, even if the facsimile software is notused or is unloaded from memory.andP;  A &quot;Z&quot; cartridge font is included free.andP;  Theproduct's client station takes up only 7Kb of conventional memory.andP;  AdvancedEZ-FaxLAN is available now in two versions - AVS96, for up to eight stations,priced at $1,400, and AVL, which has no maximum number of stations, whichcosts $1,800.andP;  Both versions include an EZ-FaxLAN 9600 bps fax-card withworkstation and server software.andP;  Entry level products are available in twoversions - ESS for up to eight stations at $500, and ESL, at $900.andO;</TEXT></DOC>